<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="76" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1668,2091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,289,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
The new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Aver." authorityName="Aver." box="[682,870,1668,1694]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tatianae">
<emphasis box="[682,805,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">B. tatianae</emphasis>
Aver.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Nguyen, K. S. &amp; Maisak, T. V." box="[904,1229,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" refId="ref11729" refString="Averyanov, L. V., Nguyen, K. S. &amp; Maisak, T. V. (2019 a) Plant diversity, flora and vegetation of Hin Nam No protected area. Lambert Academic Publishing, Saarbrucken, 431 pp." type="book" year="2019">
Averyanov 
<emphasis box="[1033,1090,1668,1694]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
(2019a: 93)
</bibRefCitation>
, differing mainly in its leaves with hairy petiole and blade, adaxial surface of blade with numerous irregular spots and without crystalloid bodies, inflorescences 
<quantity box="[390,494,1740,1767]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" unit="cm" value="5.25" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–8 cm</quantity>
long and as long as leaves, pistillate flowers with 5 tepals, glabrous ovary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
